Henry Linn SHOCK, Appellant, v. Joseph W. SANFORD, Warden, United States Penitentiary, Atlanta, Georgia, Appellee. No. 9709. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. May 28, 1941. Henry Linn Shock, in propria persona, for appellant. Lawrence S. Camp, U. S. Atty., and Harvey H. Tysinger and John J. Flynt, Jr., Asst. U. S. Attys., all of Atlanta, Ga., for appellee.

Before FOSTER, HUTCHESON, and HOLMES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
